Ok well, after reading these, I've come to the sick realization that
although I just upgraded my PC its time for MORE MORE MORE!

> -----Original Message-----
> From: Elijah Meeker [mailto:emeeker@...]
> Sent: Wednesday, July 26, 2000 9:45 AM
> To: 'eqbards@egroups.com'
> Subject: RE: [eqbards] Survey - System standards and Performance
>
>
> Computer Specs for Bards
>
> CPU: P3 700
> RAM: 256
> Video Card (and RAM): GEForce, 32
> Video Resolution: 1024x768
> Sound Card: Turtle beach sunthin
> HD speed (rpm):7200 rpm
> 'Net speed: Cable Modem
> Geographic Location: Texas, pardner
> Options enabled or disabled:
> Sky texturing: 2 layer
> Particle Effects: low because of the damn Blade of
> Fiery Lamentations
>
> as well as to see past my own effects
> Mip Mapping: off
> Clip plane distance: max except in Warsliks woods and Kurns tower
>
> How many songs can you twist? 3-4 easily, if there is is a
> lot of AE going
> on (because of the damn Blade of Fiery Lamentations) I still
> have to switch
> to overhead view to lose the lag. The BoFL will at times
> cause slightly less
> than 1 second screen freezes.
>
> Do you slow down when it rains? no, sometimes I get a little
> sad, but I have
> some nice Earl Grey Tea and read some Rainer Maria Rilke and
> after a while
> everything seems like it is going to be okay...
>
> How about in Unrest or Kunark? Unrest is now wonderfully huntable
>
>
> Tszaaz/Tsengu
